The grips show average wear – overall, this is about an 80-85% gun with a very nice bore and strong rifling. This is a very collectible and very nice First-Gen SAA, this gun belongs in a very good collection. As mentioned, the Colt Letter, when received, will go to the buyer, we do not have any accessories for this gun..Thanks for checking..

title: For Sale/Trade:  Custom/Sporterized 8mm Mauser 98 ***PRICE DROP***
postcontent: Pretty little Mauser "sporter"... done well.  Its an older rifle, but everything is in good condition and some good hand work has gone into this one.  Nice straight grained walnut stock with raised cheekpiece and hand cut checkering.  Bore looks good for age, rifling still crisp.  Step down 24" original barrel that has been turned to almost what I would consider a "mountain contour", lightweight style to it.  Front site post and front ring on action are hand stippled.  Bent and polished bolt handle.  Buehler low profile safety installed.  Red "grind to fit" 1/2" butt pad added, but also comes with the original sporterized metal butt plate.  Drilled and tapped and comes with Weaver bases.  Nice old sling studs added with sling holders.  Rifle is fully bedded... but its an older job.  Its NOT a beauty queen... but a lot better than many older jobs on customized/sporterized 8mm Mausers I have seen out there.  Bluing 80-85%? (floor plate/trigger guard is pretty much "in the white")  Stock 85%+? I will not ship... I prefer local folks.  Text questions to REDACTED.  Ask for more pictures... I can take good close ups of anything and shoot it to you...

title: For Sale:  VERY RARE!  30-30 WIN ACCELERATOR 55GR

postcontent:
Safely use your trusted old winchester 94 or marlin 336 for varmint and small game, with a 55gr bullet traveling at 3,400 fps out of your .30-30. The idea behind the "Accelerator" was to provide the hunter a practical means of taking small game with a large caliber rifle, without destroying all the eatable meat. In effect, the hunter was using high-speed .22 caliber bullets, fired from a standard .30 caliber rifle. This worked particularly well when the hunter wanted to carry just one rifle. By carrying both .30 caliber ammunition and sabot-loaded ammunition, the hunter had the equivalent of two guns-in-one.

Rare, this load isn't made by Remington anymore.

title: For Sale:  Winchester Model 1912
location: Mobile Hwy Brownsville area Pensacola FL, Pensacola, Florida
postcontent:
The Winchester Model 1912 (also commonly known as the Model 12, or M12) is an internal-hammer, pump-action, shotgun with an external tube magazine. Popularly-named the Perfect Repeater at its introduction, it largely set the standard for pump action shotguns over its 51 year high-rate production life. From August 1912 until first discontinued by Winchester in May 1964,
Unlike most modern pump-action shotguns, the Winchester Model 12 had no trigger disconnector. Like the earlier Model 1897, it too fired each time the action closed with the trigger depressed. That and its 6-shot capacity made it effective for close-combat. As fast as one could pump the action, another shot would be fired.
The United States armed forces used various versions of the Model 12 in World War I, World War II, Korea, and in the early part of the Vietnam War, until inventory was exhausted after the Model 12's initial production ceased in 1964

The year of manufacture for serial number 1260806 is 1951.
